LLVM's atomic file writes (llvm::sys::fs::TempFile, used by FileOutputBuffer and
therefore by llvm-rc/windres, lld, llvm-objcopy, etc.) write to a temp file and
then rename it onto the destination. On Windows TempFile::keep() renames through
rename_handle() -- a HANDLE-based rename that needs SetFileInformationByHandle
(Vista+); its only fallback recovers the source path via GetFinalPathNameByHandleW
(also Vista+). Both are absent on Windows XP/2000, so the fallback dies with
ERROR_CALL_NOT_IMPLEMENTED ("This function is not supported on this system") and
every .res/.o/.exe atomic write fails -- e.g. `windres foo.rc -O coff foo.res`
aborts right after the (now-working) preprocess step.

The pre-Vista pieces are already in place: llvm-support-pre-vista.patch makes the
public fs::rename() route through MoveFileExW by PATH (XP-safe), and TempFile::
create() already reacts to setDeleteDisposition() failing on XP by setting
RemoveOnClose=true and installing a RemoveFileOnSignal crash handler (so the temp
is still cleaned up on abnormal exit). We deliberately keep setDeleteDisposition()
returning ERROR_CALL_NOT_IMPLEMENTED for exactly that reason -- turning it into a
no-op would drop the crash-cleanup signal handler AND leave keep() on the broken
rename_handle() path.

So the only fix needed is in TempFile::keep(): when RemoveOnClose is set (the
pre-Vista path), rename by path with fs::rename(TmpName, Name) instead of the
handle-based rename_handle(). The temp is opened with FILE_SHARE_DELETE, so it can
be renamed while its handle is still open. The no-argument keep() likewise skips
the disposition-clearing call, which was never applied on XP.

This file (llvm/lib/Support/Path.cpp) is cross-platform; the changes are inside
its existing #ifdef _WIN32 blocks, so non-Windows hosts are unaffected.

diff --git a/llvm/lib/Support/Path.cpp b/llvm/lib/Support/Path.cpp
index 1e2d53196..04cde8747 100644
--- a/llvm/lib/Support/Path.cpp
+++ b/llvm/lib/Support/Path.cpp
@@ -1287,7 +1287,13 @@ Error TempFile::keep(const Twine &Name) {
       RemoveOnClose ? std::error_code() : setDeleteDisposition(H, false);
   bool ShouldDelete = false;
   if (!RenameEC) {
-    RenameEC = rename_handle(H, Name);
+    // Pre-Vista: RemoveOnClose is set when setDeleteDisposition() failed (no
+    // SetFileInformationByHandle). rename_handle()'s only fallback there is
+    // MoveFileEx via GetFinalPathNameByHandleW, which is likewise unavailable,
+    // so rename by path instead -- fs::rename() uses MoveFileExW, and the temp
+    // is opened FILE_SHARE_DELETE so it can be renamed while still open.
+    RenameEC = RemoveOnClose ? fs::rename(TmpName, Name)
+                             : rename_handle(H, Name);
     // If rename failed because it's cross-device, copy instead
     if (RenameEC ==
       std::error_code(ERROR_NOT_SAME_DEVICE, std::system_category())) {
@@ -1333,8 +1339,11 @@ Error TempFile::keep() {

 #ifdef _WIN32
   auto H = reinterpret_cast<HANDLE>(_get_osfhandle(FD));
-  if (std::error_code EC = setDeleteDisposition(H, false))
-    return errorCodeToError(EC);
+  // Pre-Vista (RemoveOnClose set): the delete disposition was never applied
+  // (no SetFileInformationByHandle), so there is nothing to clear.
+  if (!RemoveOnClose)
+    if (std::error_code EC = setDeleteDisposition(H, false))
+      return errorCodeToError(EC);
 #endif
   sys::DontRemoveFileOnSignal(TmpName);

